Unjustifiable, no, but it would certainly be hard. Rail needs straight and flat alignments to compete with road transport. This is difficult to achieve in mountainous terrain like Donegal. Doesn't mean we shouldn't do it but it means that other projects through easier terrain and larger population centres will probably out compete it for funding in the short term.
